node.text:
I am more passionate than ever that this is our time as leaders to lead! 

From our own growth to our families, our businesses, and our communities – they all depend on strong leadership values and principles. Now is the time to lean in together and build a better and brighter future. We need you!

That is why I am excited to invite YOU to join me and some of my closest friends for our most prestigious leadership and personal growth event of the year – Live2Lead – October 8th in Atlanta, GA.

The lineup of Speakers is a proven group whose heart is built around adding value and guiding you on your leadership journey. We are for you! 

This year’s speakers include:

Ed Mylett - @edmylett 
Jamie Kern Lima - @jamiekernlima 
Valorie Burton - @valorieburton 
Jeff Henderson - @jefferyhenderson 
John Maxwell - @johncmaxwell 

And newly added speakers:

Joel Manby - @joelmanby_official 
Tim Elmore - @growingleaders 
Don Yaeger - @donyaeger 

How do you make your leadership count?

Every one of you, you have a journey to take.
Your first step is your most important step.
You grow with intention.
You don’t go up to the top, you grow up to the top.

“You are ONE decision away from shifting your life from where it is right now to a totally different place” – @edmylett 

“So often our setbacks are setups” – @jamiekernlima 

“What if you interrupted that pattern of thinking and said what do I want that takes your energy and focus off of the problem and begins to focus you on a solution” – @valorieburton 

“Commitment will get you to the starting line. Consistency will get you to the finish line” – @jefferyhenderson 

Join us this YEAR – and be IN THE ROOM on October 8th in Atlanta, GA 
Seating is LIMITED so be sure to secure your tickets today. 

Register through link in Bio.

Live2Lead
One place to hear World-Class Leaders
One place to help you grow in your Leadership
One place to help you transform your life and the world around you.

Success is a series of steps – not one giant leap.
You were born, you were created for your LIFE to count!

Your Friend,

John Maxwell

node.text:
⁣
⁣
Here’s my five-step process for equipping people:⁣
⁣
⁃ Step 1: I do it.⁣
⁃ Step 2: I do it while you watch me.⁣
⁃ Step 3: You do it while I watch you.⁣
⁃ Step 4: You do it.⁣
⁃ Step 5: You do it and somebody is with you.⁣
⁣
When equipping people, most leaders stop at step 4. But the best leaders who have tapped into their multiplication potential, go all the way to step 5.

node.text: In honor of all the fathers today, I wanted to share tip on remembering names. My father impressed upon me at an early age the truth of what Dale Carnegie taught, “The sweetest sound in a person’s ear is the sound of their own name.”

node.text: Leaders listen, leaders learn, and then leaders lead. It’s the listening and the learning that provides the cues of how to lead people. Don’t forget these foundational principles during difficult times. Your people need you to let them know (especially during difficult times) that you understand what they are going through.

node.title: Before I can lead you, I have to connect with you.

I am blown away by the generosity of @faithpromise donating 4,000 copies of #ChangeYourWorld to all the teachers in Knox County, Tennessee! Wow! 

Educators all across the globe have been through such a difficult time because of COVID-19. If you are an educator, I want to say thank you from the bottom of my heart. You are true heroes. And you are on the frontlines of transformation in our communities as you influence the next generation of leaders. Keep up the good work!

Prices go up TONIGHT! Go to L2LATL.com to reserve your seat now!

What a great challenge from my friend @ValorieBurton – operate with optimism! 
#FlashbackFriday 😀 This clip was taken from #Live2Lead 2015 when Valorie delivered a powerful message on how our thinking greatly effects our leadership.

Join me, along with Valorie and many other amazing communicators this year for Live2Lead in Atlanta, GA on October 8th. Tickets are available through the link in my bio!

As you lead people, how optimistic are you?

VALORIE BURTON Certified Personal and Executive Coach and Bestselling Author'.

node.text:
@ValorieBurton is joining us at #Live2Lead 2021! Get to know a little bit more about my friend:

Life strategist, and international speaker, Valorie is CEO of the Coaching and Positive Psychology (CaPP) Institute. Her life-changing message has an intriguing, research-based emphasis in the pioneering field of applied positive psychology - the study of what happens when things go right with us. Her company provides coaching, coach training, and resilience training and has served clients in all 50 states and 20 countries on six continents. She has appeared regularly on the TODAY Show, CNN, Dr. Oz, and Essence, and has spoken for hundreds of organizations around the globe. She was named one of the top 60 motivational speakers in America and one of the Top 100 Thought Leaders in the field of personal development.

Join us LIVE & IN THE ROOM with Valorie and many other incredible leaders on October 8th in Atlanta, GA.
Link in bio to register!

node.text: The highest reward that you have for growth is not what you get from it, but what you become by it.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Wisdom w is knowing what do to next.'.

node.text:
Wisdom is knowing what to do next.
How wise are the voices you listen to?

Skill is knowing how to do it.
How skilled are the hands you’re learning from?

Virtue is doing it.
How strong are your values that drive your behavior?

Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Skill is knowing how to do it.'.
Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Virtue is doing it.'.
Photo shared by John C. Maxwell on August 01, 2021 tagging @luisabinader, @juanvereecken, and @jmarkcole. May be an image of 8 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Enjoyed spending time today with @luisabinader - the President of Dominican Republic - and his team. Big things on the horizon! 

Thankful for @jmarkcole @juanvereecken for being in the room and helping us launch Transformation Roundtables across all streams of influence in the DR. 

Love what I do and love who I do it with!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'THERE'S A BIG DIFFERENCE BETWEEN PROBLEM SPOTTING AND PROBLEM SOLVING.'.

node.text: Set yourself apart by solving the problems you spot.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 8 people and people standing.

node.text: I know @tracimorrow is excited for #Live2Lead 2021 – the question is, are you? Join us LIVE & IN THE ROOM on October 8th in Atlanta, GA. Learn more through the link in my bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on July 30, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'PASSION ALLOWS YOU TO PUT EVERYTHING YOU'VE GOT INTO EVERYTHING YOU DO.'.

node.text:
In this week’s episode of the #MaxwellPodcast, we begin a new series on “Questions I Ask Myself as a Leader.” Tune in to hear me share the questions I pose to myself to make sure I am continually growing and adding value to others. 

When we don’t ask ourselves good questions as leaders, we miss out on identifying potential blind spots in our leadership and opportunities to grow.

Link in bio! Episode available everywhere today.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The leader's greatest hindrance ispride.'.

node.text: Pride distorts the picture until you lose common sense, which causes you to lose common ground with people, and then there’s no connecting. Leaders: be humble!
